FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1781387267
OL,3,CHistoric landmark site to be renamed
OL,4,Cin rebrand project
OL,6,FThe SS Great Britain is known as the
OL,7,Ffirst modern ship. When the vessel was
OL,8,Flaunched in 1843, it was called 'the
OL,9,Fgreatest experiment since creation' as
OL,10,FBrunel constructed it from iron and
OL,11,Ffitted it with the most powerful
OL,12,Fengine yet used at sea.
OL,14,FUntil that point, sea travel in wooden
OL,15,Fsailing vessels had always been slow,
OL,16,Funpredictable and highly dangerous,
OL,17,Fbut the SS Great Britain combined
OL,18,Fsteam and sail, meaning when the wind
OL,19,Fdropped, the engines kicked in.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
